This paper deals with the capacity of non-coherent fading channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the prediction error of the fading process, which is related to statistical inference (cs.SI) and signal processing (cs.NI). The use of IID inputs and block-constant magnitude inputs suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.MM) and optimization (cs.LG).
